<paragraph id="84FF948AACBD8C9EF74DFC5A7600E90C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15CE9EB8EC78F693A519D43851A5FB7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="45B6B23D864C9F568D00138277249686" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia dictyospora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dictyospora">
<emphasis id="E511B8D5E9491756095D7E24C08A06B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia dictyospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
M.E. Barr et al., Mycotaxon 29: 196 (1987)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="37B6E8AAD3FD80A282EBAD9C01D6D5AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="552D830B276B4A63EE0D51293C4AA525" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E71C718C48187673CDA59207DD11066" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="2850D4D993CA53F198AE428A5C9A898E" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ECEFC82CAA67950310FFFA2FE86B99D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced by Barr (1987) and is typified by 
<taxonomicName id="3D742192D889D5156B90ADBD084F719E" genus="G." lsidName="G. dictyospora" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dictyospora">
<emphasis id="5B584232DC98D60DCA629E5D21AEC9F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G. dictyospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The fungus infects branches of 
<taxonomicName id="1E7BD202C8B29289A5DF38C3DD6BA1DB" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Polylepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polylepis sericea" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis id="FBB3EF914B3EEDAB241DEC35A3726059" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Polylepis sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wedd. (
<taxonomicName id="A48DEB911E062D7B06536780138FA225" genus="Rosaceae" lsidName="Rosaceae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="689DF95AF64B494C155E2AE896E78763" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rosaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and produces conspicuous (3-14 cm in diam.) and black ascostromata. 
<taxonomicName id="F4E3886F3EE6CD61817AECB2E2290740" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91C898CEA4DD35ECA9B64A3201B212EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="A6284C04F69037A2947ECF4D7C7E8C21" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Shiraiaceae" genus="Shiraia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Shiraia" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4D8197BCB903D14D89F2799D2F7344F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shiraia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having muriform ascospores, however, it differs by its black and larger ascostromata. 
<bibRefCitation id="7173F8DAF7F244D1D4334787E895420E" author="Kirk, PM" journalOrPublisher="CABI, Wallingford" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Kirk, PM, Cannon, PF, Minter, DW, Stalpers, JA, 2008. Dictionary of the Fungi (10th edn). . CABI, Wallingford" title="Dictionary of the Fungi (10 th edn)." year="2008">Kirk et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="6CEC08DF644D94D31D8788AC3AA01D9D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3158/1557.1" author="Lumbsch, HT" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Life and Earth Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 64" refId="B37" refString="Lumbsch, HT, Huhndorf, SM, 2010. Myconet Volume 14. Part one. Outline of Ascomycota-2009. Part Two. Notes on Ascomycete Systematics. Nos. 4751-5113. . Fieldiana Life and Earth Sciences 1: 1 - 64" title="Myconet Volume 14. Part one. Outline of Ascomycota- 2009. Part Two. Notes on Ascomycete Systematics. Nos. 4751 - 5113." url="https://doi.org/10.3158/1557.1" volume="1" year="2010">Lumbsch and Huhndorf (2010)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="6521C00C7A41D2CD114D797802280247" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="381F0CFC47B363A9995731ADCECF6DBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Grandigallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4E863F259F53D8D46C33CC2B07DB400E" class="Dothideomycetes" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="class">Dothideomycetes</taxonomicName>
, genera 
<emphasis id="D19D2E03EFDAA43EF3C3A1ECCD4EEE57" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">incertae sedis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B123F4E111DAF065D7A9BC3F33CA6B2B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" author="Ariyawansa, HA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="35 - 47" refId="B2" refString="Ariyawansa, HA, Kang, JC, Alias, SA, Chukeatirote, E, Hyde, KD, 2013. Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis). . Phytotaxa 147: 35 - 47" title="Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" volume="147" year="2013">Ariyawansa et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
re-examined the type material and transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="B99FE370F7C4250C26CEF82C3917D337" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="BFD1C4E7AC2A0EBD6127696CC3C807A9" lsidName="" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="order">Pleosporales</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="245558B7317FBC1CB01EE2A126CA5B0B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0309-2" author="Wijayawardene, NN" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 55" refId="B64" refString="Wijayawardene, NN, Crous, PW, Kirk, PM, Hawksworth, DL, Boonmee, S, Braun, U, Chomnunti, P, Dai, DQ, D'souza, MJ, Diederich, P, Dissanayake, A, Doilom, M, Hongsanan, S, Jones, EBG, Groenewald, JZ, Jayawardena, R, Lawrey, JD, Liu, JK, Luecking, R, Madrid, H, Manamgoda, DS, Muggia, L, Nelsen, MP, Phookamsak, R, Suetrong, S, Tanaka, K, Thambugala, KM, Wikee, S, Zhang, Y, Aptroot, A, Ariyawansa, HA, Bahkali, AH, Bhat, JD, Gueidan, C, De Hoog, GS, Knudsen, K, McKenzie, EHC, Miller, AN, Mortimer, PE, Wanasinghe, DN, Phillips, AJL, Raja, HA, Slippers, B, Shivas, RS, Taylor, JE, Wang, Y, Woudenberg, JHC, Piatek, M, Cai, L, Jaklitsch, WM, Hyde, KD, 2014. Naming and outline of Dothideomycetes. (2014) including proposals for the protection or suppression of generic names. . Fungal Diversity 69: 1 - 55" title="Naming and outline of Dothideomycetes. (2014) including proposals for the protection or suppression of generic names." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0309-2" volume="69" year="2014">Wijayawardene et al. (2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="38259791A92913F58C1245DE93B5D3D2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/8/7/9" author="Wijayawardene, NN" journalOrPublisher="Mycosphere" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="934 - 950" refId="B65" refString="Wijayawardene, NN, Papizadeh, M, Phillips, AJL, Wanasinghe, DN, Bhat, DJ, Weerahewa, HLD, Shenoy, BD, Wang, Y, Huang, YQ, 2017. Mycosphere Essays 19: Recent advances and future challenges in taxonomy of coelomycetous fungi. . Mycosphere 8: 934 - 950" title="Mycosphere Essays 19: Recent advances and future challenges in taxonomy of coelomycetous fungi." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/8/7/9" volume="8" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="59706B90BB40EF1FECA1BE40AA00CEDE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-018-0394-8" author="Wijayawardene, NN" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="167 - 263" refId="B66" refString="Wijayawardene, NN, Hyde, KD, Lumbsch, HT, Liu, JK, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Ekanayaka, AH, Tian, Q, Phookamsak, R, 2018. Outline of Ascomycota: 2017. . Fungal Diversity 88: 167 - 263" title="Outline of Ascomycota: 2017." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-018-0394-8" volume="88" year="2018">2018</bibRefCitation>
) accepted this placement.
</paragraph>
